    "recap_headline": "",
    "recap_text": "KENNESAW, GA. \u2013\nThe Liberty Flames scored four runs in the first and never looked back, sailing past the Kennesaw Owls 11-5 in a CUSA contest on Saturday at Mickey Dunn Stadium. With wins in the first two games of the series, the Flames capture their first conference series of 2026.\nCenter fielder\nJosh Campos\nhomered for the second straight day, his fifth of the season, and left fielder\nNick Barone\ndrove in three runs with a triple and a sacrifice fly for the Flames.\nIn addition, Liberty third baseman\nJaxon Sorenson\nhad two hits, one a double, and an RBI, scoring four runs in the game.\u00a0 \u00a0 Entering the fourth inning with two men on, right-hander\nJake Potts\npitched three innings of scoreless relief, retiring all nine batters he faced to record the win.\nLiberty moves to 3-2 in CUSA play and 15-7 overall. Kennesaw State falls to 1-4 in CUSA and 9-10 overall.\nBox Score Highlights\nRecords:\nLiberty (15-7, 3-2 CUSA); Kennesaw State (9-10, 1-4 CUSA)\nLocation:\nMickey Dunn Stadium (Kennesaw, Ga.)\nWP:\nJake Potts\n(1-1) \u00a0|\nLP:\nJayden Summerville (0-1) |\nSV:\nCooper Harrington\n(2)\nScoring Summary\n1\nst\n\u2013 LIBERTY \u2013 Sorenson reaches on a fielder's choice, Marsh scores, 1-0\n1\nst\n\u2013 LIBERTY \u2013 Barone triples, Sorenson and Drumm score, 3-0\n1\nst\n\u2013 LIBERTY \u2013 Barone scores on a wild pitch, 4-0\n4\nth\n\u2013 KSU \u2013 McCollum flies out, McGee scores, 4-1\n6\nth\n\u2013 LIBERTY \u2013 DeCandido singles, Sorenson scores, 5-1\n8\nth\n\u2013 LIBERTY \u2013 Hvidsten doubles, Sorenson scores, 6-1\n8\nth\n\u2013 LIBERTY \u2013 Campos homers, Hvidsten and Swofford score, 9-1\n8\nth\n\u2013 KSU \u2013 McGee singles, Posey and Cole score, 9-3\n9\nth\n\u2013 LIBERTY \u2013 Barone flies out, Jaffe scores, 10-3\n9\nth\n\u2013 LIBERTY \u2013 Swofford reaches on an error, Sorenson scores, 11-3\n9\nth\n\u2013 KSU \u2013 Posey homers, Alig scores, 11-5\nNotable Numbers\n- Each team had eight hits in the game. Kennesaw State committed three errors.\n- The Flames left seven men on base. The Owls left five.\n- Liberty took advantage of nine walks issued by Kennesaw State pitching.\n- Flames reliever\nCooper Harrington\n, the fourth Liberty pitcher to take the mound in the game, earned a save with three innings of work. He allowed four runs on five hits over the three innings. The right-hander struck out seven and did not walk a batter.\n- Kennesaw State starter Jayden Summerville takes the loss. He gave up four runs on three hits over three innings, striking out five and walking two.\n- Catcher Aaron Posey went 3-for-4 with a home run for the Owls.\nBeyond the Box Score\n- With wins in the first two games of the three-game series, Liberty takes the series and will look for the sweep tomorrow.\n- The Flames move to 6-2 on the road this season.\n- Sorenson collects a multi-hit game for the second straight day. The third baseman now has five multi-hit games on the season. He also tied his career-high with four runs in the game, tying a four-run day in a victory over Princeton on March 16, 2025.\n- With a single in the top of the sixth inning, first baseman\nRiley DeCandido\nhas reached base in 11 consecutive games.\n- With his fifth home run of the season, Campos tied DeCandido for the team lead in home runs.\nUp Next\nLiberty will go for the series sweep against Kennesaw State tomorrow. The first pitch at Mickey Dunn Stadium is scheduled for 1 p.m.",
